"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:2.10.1\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">2.10.1</span> 标题：大盾（large shield）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">经文出处</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">来：צִנָּה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：tsinah)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:7\">1SA 17:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:41\">1SA 17:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs10:16\">1KI 10:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs10:16\">1KI 10:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:9\">1CH 12:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:25\">1CH 12:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:35\">1CH 12:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr9:15\">2CH 9:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr9:15\">2CH 9:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr11:12\">2CH 11:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr14:7\">2CH 14:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr25:5\">2CH 25:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps5:13\">PSA 5:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:2\">PSA 35:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps91:4\">PSA 91:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer46:3\">JER 46:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek23:24\">EZK 23:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek26:8\">EZK 26:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek38:4\">EZK 38:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek39:9\">EZK 39:9</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希：ἀσπιδίσκη</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：aspidiskē)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc4:57\">1MA 4:57</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希：ἀσπίς</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：aspis)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jdt9:7\">JDT 9:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Wis5:19\">WIS 5:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir29:13\">SIR 29:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir37:5\">SIR 37:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc6:39\">1MA 6:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc14:24\">1MA 14:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc15:18\">1MA 15:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc15:20\">1MA 15:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Macc5:3\">2MA 5:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Macc15:11\">2MA 15:11</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希：κάλυμμα</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：kalumma)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc4:6\">1MA 4:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc6:2\">1MA 6:2</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希：θυρεός</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：thureos)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:16\">EPH 6:16</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0386_large_shield.jpg\" alt=\"亚述巴尼拔（Ashurbanipal）狩猎狮子时士兵手持的大盾牌（大英博物馆，10a展厅）\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">亚述巴尼拔（Ashurbanipal）狩猎狮子时士兵手持的大盾牌（大英博物馆，10a展厅） (© Johnbod, CC BY-SA 4.0, via Wikimedia Commons)</figcaption></figure>大盾是一个椭圆形的长盾牌，大约有一个人的高度，用来保护人的全身。大盾可以是木制、金属制，或者用木架撑着皮革制成，甚至是用木条或芦苇编织而成。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">用途</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>握持这种大盾时，用一只手握住大盾背面的索带。右手拿剑的战士会用左手持盾，反之亦然。战士把盾牌挡在自己和对手之间，以遮挡刀剑、枪矛或棍棒的攻击，也用来阻挡箭、石头、投枪之类的投掷武器。在大卫打败巨人歌利亚的故事中（<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:0\">1SA 17:0</a> ），有个仆人站在歌利亚的前面，手持着巨人的大盾牌。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻译</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>有些语言将“盾”译作：“人打仗时携带的护具”，或“为抵挡敌人攻击而携带的护具”。在一些以“盾”为喻的经文中，翻译者可以既保留盾的保护含意，又不把实际的装备翻译出来；例如，在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps91:4\">PSA 91:4</a> ，原文字面意为“他的信实是大盾牌和小圆盾”，<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 采用了直译，然而也可以译为，“上帝信守他的应许，必要保护你。”</p>\n<p>希伯来文<em>tsinah</em> 有时喻指上帝是保护者（参<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps5:13\">PSA 5:13</a> ［《和》5:12］和<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps91:4\">PSA 91:4</a> ，以及<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">2.10.2 小盾、小圆盾 (small shield, buckler)&lt;REALIA:2.10.2&gt;</a> 中的讨论）。</p>\n<p>在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek26:8\">EZK 26:8</a> 中，希伯来文<em>tsinah</em> 表示一个特别大的盾，称为移动防弹盾（参<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">2.19.8 移动防弹盾 (mantelet)&lt;REALIA:2.19.8&gt;</a> ），置于正在攻城的士兵头上或前面。虽然这个希伯来文词语是单数，但它的遮挡功能通常是由很多面盾排在一起来实现的。因此，这节经文的最后一部分可译作，“做成一道盾牌墙攻击你”（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 直译），或“竖起一排排的盾牌围住你”（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Contemporary English Version\">CEV</abbr> 直译）。</p>\n<p>在《七十士译本》中，希腊文<em>kalumma</em> 指会幕中的幔子或覆盖会幕中器具的布。在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc4:6\">1MA 4:6</a> ，几乎所有译本都将其译作某件防护性“盔甲”（“armor”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 、<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Contemporary English Version\">CEV</abbr> ）。在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc6:2\">1MA 6:2</a> ，有些译本译作“盾牌”（“shields”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 、<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Contemporary English Version\">CEV</abbr> ），而<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New American Bible (1970)\">NAB</abbr> 和戈尔茨坦（Goldstein）则译为“头盔”（“helmets”）。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
